Where should H and I go for vacation in late this month?
</headline>
<post author="mathgal102..." datetime="2012-02-02T07:26:00" id="p1">
We have the President's Day holiday and we don't work that Friday before so I can take my measly couple of days vacation I've earned since Key West in November and take about a week off. No other holidays til late May so I'm hoping to make the most of it. We have a $200 Southwest Credit we have to use too. I was thinking Panama City or actually driving to Charleston (9 hours but by the time we would drive to the airport, wait and fly it would be about the same and we love roadtrips) and do the SC low country.
We like nature stuff and we like the beach but not just a "lay on the beach" vacation. We like a good happy hour but not a "whole just drink vacay" like Vegas would be. Any other ideas or recs for Panama City or Charleston?
</post>
<post author="mathgal102..." datetime="2012-02-02T07:27:00" id="p2">
